14/12/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- A poll conducted by the KAPPA research agency suggests broad public support for Socialist Karolos Papoulias as president.
Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis, who leads the ruling New Democracy party, announced the idea last week.
According to results released Monday (13 December), nearly 80 per cent of respondents expressed support for Papoulias.
(ANA - 14/12/04;
MPA - 13/12/04)
